
[Richmond, 5? June 1780. JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 35 (5 June): The Speaker laid before the House a letter from the Governor, enclosing one from the President of Congress, together with a resolution of that body, concerning a Monsieur Legrass of Illinois, and several letters and papers on the subject thereof. Not located, but see Pres. Huntingtons letter to TJ, 11 May 1780, which was enclosed.]
